From cd5d82f2b9b0833cdf16e32f8006c8b7aed056ca Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: charlesmamane26-sketch <charlesmamane1826@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 14:12:54 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 02/11] fix(net,js): resolve-time SSRF guard, IP denylist, body
 cap, header filter
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

SSRF (SSRF-01/04/06, OPS-01/02/03): add canonical is_forbidden_ip (0.0.0.0/8, IPv4-mapped IPv6, ULA fc00::/7, CGNAT, NAT64, multicast, unspecified, reserved) and an SsrfDnsResolver that resolves the host, rejects any forbidden resolved address and pins the connection — closing DNS rebinding. Installed on the nav client, op_fetch_url and the dynamic-import module loader; the stealth (wreq) client now runs validate_url on the initial URL and every redirect hop (SSRF-02/03).

DoS (NAVDOS-01/02, OPS-01): cap the buffered response body (read_body_capped / OBSCURA_MAX_BODY_BYTES, default 256 MiB) on the reqwest clients; stealth pre-checks Content-Length.

OPS-HDR-01: drop forbidden request headers (Host/Cookie/Referer/Origin/Sec-*/...) that page JS must not control. OPS-04: never log the module-loader proxy URL.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

